thods, of 63.5% for the 2010-11 season and 63.4% for the 2009-10 season.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":508,"renderedHeight":388,"naturalWidth":508,"naturalHeight":388,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 479 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":10609},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m6138a1f2.gif","alt":"The figure shows the percentage of health-care personnel (HCP) who received influenza vaccination, by work setting, in the United States, during the 2009-10, 2010-11, and 2011-12 influenza seasons. According to an Internet panel survey, coverage in physician's office settings increased from 61.5% during the 2010-11 season to 67.7% during the 2011-12 season, and coverage in hospitals increased from 71.1% to 76.9%. Among long-term care facilities (LTCFs), influenza vaccination coverage was lower in 2011-12 (52.4%), compared with 2010-11 (64.4%). The 2011-12 coverage in work settings other than hospitals, physician offices, and LTCFs was higher (61.5%) than in 2010-11 (52.4%).","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":502,"renderedHeight":384,"naturalWidth":502,"naturalHeight":384,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 682 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":11781},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt"